{"type":"info-page","slug":"ijs/content/early/2011/04/08/ijs.0.029991-0.abstract","journal":"ijs","canonical":"https://www.sgmjournals.org/ijs/content/early/2011/04/08/ijs.0.029991-0.abstract","title":"International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"article abstract-view\">\n\n        <h1 id=\"article-title-1\"><em>Streptomyces brevispora</em> sp. nov. and <em>Streptomyces laculatuspora</em> sp. nov., novel actinomycetes isolated from soil</h1>\n        <div class=\"contributors\">\n          <ol class=\"contributor-list\" id=\"contrib-group-1\">\n            <li class=\"contributor\" id=\"contrib-1\"><span class=\"name\"><a class=\"name-search\" href=\"/ijs/search?author1=Tiago+D.+Zucchi&amp;sortspec=date&amp;submit=Submit\">Tiago D. Zucchi</a></span><a id=\"xref-aff-1-1\" class=\"xref-aff\" href=\"#aff-1\" name=\"xref-aff-1-1\">1</a>,</li>\n            <li class=\"contributor\" id=\"contrib-2\"><span class=\"name\"><a class=\"name-search\" href=\"/ijs/search?author1=Byung-Yong+Kim&amp;sortspec=date&amp;submit=Submit\">Byung-Yong Kim</a></span><a id=\"xref-aff-2-1\" class=\"xref-aff\" href=\"#aff-2\" name=\"xref-aff-2-1\">2</a>,</li>\n            <li class=\"contributor\" id=\"contrib-3\"><span class=\"name\"><a class=\"name-search\" href=\"/ijs/search?author1=Jenileima+D.+Kshetrimayum&amp;sortspec=date&amp;submit=Submit\">Jenileima D. Kshetrimayum</a></span><a id=\"xref-aff-3-1\" class=\"xref-aff\" href=\"#aff-3\" name=\"xref-aff-3-1\">3</a>,</li>\n            <li class=\"contributor\" id=\"contrib-4\"><span class=\"name\"><a class=\"name-search\" href=\"/ijs/search?author1=Hang-Yeon+Weon&amp;sortspec=date&amp;submit=Submit\">Hang-Yeon Weon</a></span><a id=\"xref-aff-2-2\" class=\"xref-aff\" href=\"#aff-2\" name=\"xref-aff-2-2\">2</a>,</li>\n            <li class=\"contributor\" id=\"contrib-5\"><span class=\"name\"><a class=\"name-search\" href=\"/ijs/search?author1=Soon-Wo+Kwon&amp;sortspec=date&amp;submit=Submit\">Soon-Wo Kwon</a></span><a id=\"xref-aff-2-3\" class=\"xref-aff\" href=\"#aff-2\" name=\"xref-aff-2-3\">2</a> and</li>\n            <li class=\"last\" id=\"contrib-6\"><span class=\"name\"><a class=\"name-search\" href=\"/ijs/search?author1=Michael+Goodfellow&amp;sortspec=date&amp;submit=Submit\">Michael Goodfellow</a></span><a id=\"xref-aff-3-2\" class=\"xref-aff\" href=\"#aff-3\" name=\"xref-aff-3-2\">3</a><span class=\"xref-sep\">,</span><a id=\"xref-corresp-1-1\" class=\"xref-fn\" href=\"#corresp-1\" name=\"xref-corresp-1-1\">4</a></li>\n          </ol>\n          <ol class=\"affiliation-list\">\n            <li class=\"aff\">\n              <a id=\"aff-1\" name=\"aff-1\"></a>\n              <address>\n                <sup>1</sup> ESALQ/USP;\n              </address>\n            </li>\n            <li class=\"aff\">\n              <a id=\"aff-2\" name=\"aff-2\"></a>\n              <address>\n                <sup>2</sup> National Academy of Agricultural Science;\n              </address>\n            </li>\n            <li class=\"aff\">\n              <a id=\"aff-3\" name=\"aff-3\"></a>\n              <address>\n                <sup>3</sup> University of Newcastle upon Tyne\n              </address>\n            </li>\n          </ol>\n          <ol class=\"corresp-list\">\n            <li class=\"corresp\" id=\"corresp-1\"><a class=\"rev-xref\" href=\"#xref-corresp-1-1\">↵</a><sup>4</sup> E-mail: <span class=\"em-link\"><span class=\"em-addr\">m.goodfellow{at}ncl.ac.uk</span></span></li>\n          </ol>\n\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"section abstract\" id=\"abstract-1\">\n          <h2>Abstract</h2>\n          <p id=\"p-1\">The taxonomic positions of two actinomycetes isolated from a hay meadow soil sample were determined using a polyphasic approach. The isolates had chemical and morphological properties typical of streptomycetes and formed a distinct 16S rRNA gene subclade together with the type strain of Streptomyces drozdowiczii NRRL B-24297T. DNA:DNA relatedness studies showed that the three strains belonged to different genomic species. The organisms were also distinguished using a combination of phenotypic properties. On the basis of these data it is proposed that the isolates be assigned to the genus Streptomyces as Streptomyces brevispora sp. nov. and Streptomyces laculatuspora sp. nov., with BK160T (= KACC 21093T = NCIMB 14702T) and BK166T (= KACC 20907T = NCIMB 14703T) as the respective type strains.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div><span id=\"related-urls\"></span>","alias":true}